      {
        "question": " What is the Sputum AFB and Gram Stain test? ",
        "answer": "Sputum AFB and Gram Stain test examines the sputum to check if there are acid fast bacilli (AFB) and other organisms in the sputum."
      },
      {
        "question": " Why is the test important? ",
        "answer": "The test aids in diagnosing respiratory infections especially tuberculosis (TB) and helps in the management of the infections."
      },
      {
        "question": " What are the risks and limitations of the test? ",
        "answer": "Sputum AFB test is safe and non-invasive; however, in some instance where the other infections or TB may not be detectable, it has the possibility of yielding false positive results."
      },
      {
        "question": "What do I need to do to get ready for this test? ",
        "answer": "Whenever respiratory related examinations are needed, one must provide a sputum sample within a sealed container and send it directly for lab analysis."
      }
